# Accepted IaC findings (reviewed) — see deploy/terraform/aws/README.md.
#
# AWS-0040 / AWS-0041 — EKS public endpoint. Our module makes the public
#   endpoint OPTIONAL (cluster_endpoint_public_access, default true) and, when
#   enabled, MANDATORY-CIDR-restricted: a terraform precondition refuses an
#   empty CIDR list and a variable validation refuses 0.0.0.0/0. Set
#   cluster_endpoint_public_access=false for a fully private cluster. Trivy
#   analyzes the community module's static default and cannot see the runtime
#   guard, so it flags the module file regardless.
AVD-AWS-0040
AVD-AWS-0041
# AWS-0104 — the EKS managed node group's egress. Worker nodes MUST reach the
#   internet (pull images, AWS APIs, OIDC) — this egress is required and lives
#   in the upstream terraform-aws-eks module, not our code. The RDS security
#   group we own has no unrestricted egress.
AVD-AWS-0104
# KSV-0014 — readOnlyRootFilesystem. Containers run non-root with dropped caps
#   and no privilege escalation; readOnlyRootFilesystem is a documented opt-in
#   (containerSecurityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem) rather than a default,
#   because the router persists generated pipeline docs to its image FS. Enable
#   it per-deployment after mounting writable volumes (chart README).
AVD-KSV-0014
